trans-unit.source: Provides a fast, read-only, in-memory representation of an XML document by using the XPath data model.
trans-unit.target: Gir en rask skrivebeskyttet, i minnet representasjon av en XML-dokumentet ved å bruke XPath datamodellen.

trans-unit.source: For more information about processing XML data by using the XPath data model, see the [Process XML Data Using the XPath Data Model](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) topic.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha mer informasjon om behandling av XML-dataene ved hjelp av datamodellen XPath, se den [prosessen XML-dataene ved hjelp av datamodellen XPath](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) emnet.

trans-unit.source: After the <xref:System.IO.TextReader> object has been used to load XML data, the cursor of the <xref:System.IO.TextReader> object is positioned at the end of the data.
trans-unit.target: Etter den <xref:System.IO.TextReader>objektet er brukt til å laste inn XML-dataene, markør av den <xref:System.IO.TextReader>-objektet er plassert på slutten av dataene.</xref:System.IO.TextReader> </xref:System.IO.TextReader>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.IO.TextReader> object must be reset to read through the data again.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.IO.TextReader>objektet må tilbakestilles til å lese gjennom dataene på nytt.</xref:System.IO.TextReader>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument"></xref> class from the XML data that is contained in the specified <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument"> </xref> klassen fra XML-data som finnes i det angitte <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektet.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object can be used to load a whole XML document or part of an XML document into an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>.
trans-unit.target: Et <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objekt kan brukes til å laste inn hele XML-dokument eller en del av en XML-dokumentet til en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: To load part of an XML document into an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>, position the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object on the top XML node to load data from.
trans-unit.target: Ikke laste inn en del av en XML-dokumentet til en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>, posisjon i <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objekt på øverste XML-noden ikke laste inn data fra.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>

trans-unit.source: When you create an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> by using the XPathDocument constructor, data is loaded from the current top node through all its siblings.
trans-unit.target: Når du oppretter en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>via XPathDocument konstruktøren data som er lastet inn fra den gjeldende øverste noden gjennom alle sideordnede.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>

trans-unit.source: Afterwards, the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> is positioned on the outer scope of the top XML node.
trans-unit.target: Etterpå den <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>plasseres på ytre omfanget for den øverste XML-noden.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: Alternatively, you can use the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> method to load the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> into a particular element in the XML document.
trans-unit.target: Du kan også bruke den <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>metode for å laste inn den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>til et bestemt element i XML-dokumentet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when you use the XPathDocument constructor.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker XPathDocument-konstruktøren.

trans-unit.source: - An <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object with the appropriate associated <xref:System.Xml.XmlResolver> object settings can be used to resolve entities or other references in XML data.
trans-unit.target: – En <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objekt med riktig tilknyttede <xref:System.Xml.XmlResolver>innstillinger som kan brukes til å løse enheter eller andre referanser i XML-data.</xref:System.Xml.XmlResolver> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object is positioned on a leaf node that is not valid for the root level of a document—for example, a white space or attribute node—the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object continues to read until it is positioned on a node that can be used for the root.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>-objektet er plassert på en bladnode ikke er gyldig for root-nivå for et dokument, for eksempel et mellomrom eller attributtnode – den <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektet fortsetter å lese før den er plassert på en node som kan brukes til roten.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> begins loading at this point.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>starter laster inn på dette tidspunktet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>

trans-unit.source: - To preserve white space, use the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument.%23ctor%2A> constructor that accepts an <xref:System.Xml.XmlSpace> object as a parameter.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis du vil beholde mellomrom, kan du bruke den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument.%23ctor%2A>konstruktøren aksepterer bare en <xref:System.Xml.XmlSpace>objektet som en parameter.</xref:System.Xml.XmlSpace> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument.%23ctor%2A>
